E spells like Pillars of Frost/Lightning will only cast on a max of 4 mobs at a time.<br><br>So..what spells and what strategy do I need to use to &quot;quad&quot; more than 4 mobs at a time?<br><br><br><br> <p><p ALIGN=CENTER><img src="http://personalpages.bellsouth.net/w/r/wrightpc/everquest/NeilyxDaWizofOz.jpg" ></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukeiichirn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KeiichiRN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/02 8:51:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=547.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Octa-Kite</span><hr size=1> I do Octa-kite in Raptor Isle.<br><br>Just Train throught all Raptors in big isle so 8 running after you. run run run snare 4 and run run run snare another 4 and run run run snare again if some resisted.<br><br>gathering arround so 8 raptor stick together, and start AE them. after 4 Die I will resnare and AE those remain.<br><br>I gathering them arround is since their HP is varies so will not waste mana when one or 2 Raptors dead, remain AE effect will land on other Health Raptors so no mana wasted.<br><br>you probably need 3500 mana for OctaKite Raptor Isle? CS wyreum take much less mana to kite them. Really depend on your mana pool and level, really.<br><br>Highly recommend make a magelo profile on it and check your mana pool size.<br><br>My Spell configuration.<br>Shield of Magi<br>Havrest<br>Levivation<br>Drag of Ice<br>Pillar of Flames <br>Root<br>Atol's<br>SRO evac<br>Gate<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulishan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lishan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users2.ev1.net/~kathyk/small.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/28/02 1:05:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=547.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ubah quading</span><hr size=1> I was in Tim's deep one night, and next thing I know there were two more wizzies all quading from same area.  Well this lasted for a good while, as you can figure 3 wizzies quading, and the mobs start running low fast.,  So, after a heated argument on who was here first, one of the guys gets a bit more then he can chew, so despite the fact that we were arguing, the other wizzie and me decided to help the guy out..,  We both ran ahead and snared a few, and then ran following the first guy getting all the mobs together then nuking each of us once and wiped out the whole 'train'.  This shocked us so much at how easy it was, that we all grouped up, and tried it again, this time a bit more organized..,  Shockingly, we were quading 12 mobs at a time with no problem, each helping nuke the others and resnaring if any resisted.,.  Thats when I learned.,  three wizzies in a group = nasty.., <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulunaltoadsnatcher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/28/02 4:25:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=547.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~bookfolk/_uimages/music4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ubah quading</span><hr size=1> At the spirocs I regularly quad 8 at a time.  Its childsplay, honestly.  PoF takes them out so quickly that you can keep two groups snared and do them one after another (7-8 casts total of PoF.  If you get resists you may have to resnare.  <br><br>Oh, and I need KEI to do it securely, but I have done it without KEI at lvl 51. <p><font size=-1>Lunal Toadsnatcher<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=163741" target="_blank">Gnome Channeler of the Noble Cow (51)</a><BR>Tholuxe Paells</font><BR><font size=-2>Leader of <i><a href="http://pub63.ezboard.com/btheelectoftholuxepaells" target="_blank">The Elect</a></i></font><BR><font size=-1>"<i>Nuke em from point blank range.  Its the only way to be sure</i>."</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukaladun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaladun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/29/02 5:26:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=547.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ubah quading</span><hr size=1> At the spirocs and realized 'Damnit - no steelskin up'. So i run to one of the corners of the ramps and call it up. Proven's on me. Great. No batwings for levi by the way so this just makes me really stupid. I decide that I wasn't going to be outsted by a frigging bird - so I run ALL the way up into the treehouse. (My steelskin has long since worn off from all the incidental stomping and backstabbing) I turn around and flee like only a black man can. (Erudite - back off) I finally get out safe with like a bubble of health left... and decided to go for it.<br><br>I turn around and there are no less than 15 Spirocs on my black ass. <br><br>I almost wet myself. <br><br>Hell. I'm a wizard. I'm level 51. I'm badass. I'm a black wizard too boot. A black level 51 wizard WITH KEI.<br><br>Dropped em all save one. Was the best xp I've ever seen in my life.... and I loved it. Word of warning. You get stunned once - you're screwed.<br><br>Atol's lasts long enough for you to snare 2-3 groups of mobs and blast one down and half of the second usually before it starts wearing off. *Praises the new Pillar of Frost* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uacillatemzoso.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Acillatem Zoso</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/30/02 1:39:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=547.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ubah quading</span><hr size=1> Keiich pretty much summed up how I do it.<br><br>I first learned how to do this when a Blue Team BRD (I play PvP and u cant kill people on same team) decided to try and train me and XP kill me so he could have all the raptors.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>So here I am with 8 raptors on me - he Selo's away and I killed them all out of necessity.  Thats when I realized the &quot;efficiency&quot; in doing 8 at one time.  When doing a quad u normally kill 2 raptors and then you just WASTE two &quot;possible&quot; targets.  By octi-kiting you have 4 fresh targest to start filling up slots.<br><br>I'm a HUM WIZ - I have 228 INT WITH C3 (ya ya ya I wear a shitload of resist gear), I'd guess I might have low 3k mana pool.  <br><br>I hafta kill the first quad - I resnare after I kill 4 mobs.  Then I count 23 paces out and Harvest.....plenty of time to not get beat on.  Then I finish the second quad and revel in my blue bubble of XP I got in just 5 short minutes! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>6 minutes later FM and ready to do small isle.  Fastest XP I ever seen - even beats out AE groups (except the rare ones where you get the 40+ pulls all the time). <p>"Those that can, do.  Those that cannot, summon pets."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukeiichirn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KeiichiRN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/1/02 9:44:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=547.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Octa-Kite</span><hr size=1> Ding, Level 60 with 9 AA,<br><br>Played 174, 7 hours.<br><br>God I am a lazy Wizard.<br><br>Btw, if you didn't aware, if you gather say 8 Raptors behind you and all stay with in your AE spell range. they they are said in a queue that the first four will always to get hit by your AE spell no matter which raptor you target. <br><br>for example. a-b-c-d-e-f-g-h raptors following you. even if you target the Raptor G,  a,b,c,d will always get hit by your pillar AE first, if a and b dead, then c,d,e,f will be next on list.<br><br>that why you won't waste half of your mana since your are always hitting 4 targets instead of 3 or 2. <br><br>of course you better have decent mana pool if you going to do kite more then 4 mobs.<br><br>----------------------------------------------------<br><br>Also Tried to do stupid thing last night before Ding.<br><br>I bring a enchanter level 57 to raptor isle. then Kite 15 ratpors and try to stun them all by chanter and I cast PBAE. <br>Result: I manage to cast 2 or 3 AE at least before I log on my cleric and port cleric to SRO. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukeiichirn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KeiichiRN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/1/02 10:11:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=547.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Octa-Kite</span><hr size=1> amendment:<br>God! I just remember it is amazing that I didn't snare myself once from 59 to 60 only with 111-120 MR Since I cast Atol's at very tight range basically the snare will hit myself every time I need to snare second pile of 4 or Raptor resisted snare.<br><br>My 60 Guildie with 200+mr and snared himself in Grey muahahaa <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=547.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=547.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=547.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=547.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.threadControl?topicID=547.topic><img src=htt